ENTRY       EC 3.2.1.185                Enzyme
NAME        non-reducing end beta-L-arabinofuranosidase;
            HypBA1
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Glycosylases;
            Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
SYSNAME     beta-L-arabinofuranoside non-reducing end beta-L-arabinofuranosidase
REACTION    beta-L-arabinofuranosyl-(1->2)-beta-L-arabinofuranose + H2O = 2 beta-L-arabinofuranose [RN:R10346]
ALL_REAC    R10346
SUBSTRATE   beta-L-arabinofuranosyl-(1->2)-beta-L-arabinofuranose [CPD:C20568];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     beta-L-arabinofuranose [CPD:C20569]
COMMENT     The enzyme, which was identified in the bacterium Bifidobacterium longum JCM1217, removes the beta-L-arabinofuranose residue from the non-reducing end of multiple substrates, including beta-L-arabinofuranosyl-hydroxyproline (Ara-Hyp), Ara2-Hyp, Ara3-Hyp, and beta-L-arabinofuranosyl-(1->2)-1-O-methyl-beta-L-arabinofuranose.
            In the presence of 1-alkanols, the enzyme demonstrates transglycosylation activity, retaining the anomeric configuration of the arabinofuranose residue. cf. EC 3.2.1.55, non-reducing end alpha-L-arabinofuranosidase
